text.tspan: Open defecation in rural areas vs. urban areas
Open defecation refers defecating in the open, such as in fields, forest, bushes, open bodies of water, on beaches, in
other open spaces or disposed of with solid waste.
Source: WHO/UNICEF Joint Monitoring Programme (JMP) for Water Supply and Sanitation
